that presently occupies over four and a half million square kilometers straddling the eurasian landmass and the malay archipelago today southeast asia is home to more than half a billion people who manifest a substantial diversity of ethnicity polity language religion and sub culture southeast asia also boasts a vibrant economy with a gdp exceeding us $1 billion in 2006 and steady annual growth besides being the site of several thriving national economies the lee kong chian nus stanford initiative on southeast asia brings together two vibrant research centers the national university of singapore and stanford university the support of infrastructures for research at both universities the faculty of arts and social sciences at nus and the southeast asia forum seaf in the walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center shorenstein aparc at stanford promises that this synergistic collaboration will do much to raise the visibility extent and quality of scholarship on contemporary southeast asia contact donald k emmerson funding provided by the lee foundation events & presentations only 5 recent upcoming are displayed more events & presentations a stake in the heart of lipset's law indonesia versus modernization theory april 8 2009 seminar mark thompson late democratizers developmentalism in pacific asia march 2 2009 seminar mark thompson mobilized workers vs morphing capital challenging global supply chains in vietnam november 17 2008 lecture angie ngoc tran muslim politics in southeast asia democratic islam hijacked or re invigorated may 1 2008 special event robert w hefner schooling islam madrasas and the remaking of muslim modernity april 30 2008 special event robert w hefner search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages research news southeast asian studies at stanford a rising profile august 6 2008 seaf news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for inter